  "prompt": "Can we use 'the' before the name of any country other than Netherlands?",
  "response": "Yes, you can use \"the\" before the names of certain countries, although it is not common for most. Examples include:\n\n1. The United States (of America)\n2. The United Kingdom\n3. The Philippines\n4. The Bahamas\n5. The Maldives\n6. The Gambia\n7. The Dominican Republic\n8. The Czech Republic (although \"Czechia\" is also used without \"the\")\n\nThese countries typically have names that include a common noun or descriptor that makes the use of \"the\" grammatically appropriate. For most other country names, \"the\" is not used.",
